Female. Total length 7.5–10.3 . Carapace 2.5 –4.0 long, 2.9–3.5 wide. Length of the first patella + tibia 3.9–5.2 . Epigyne strongly sclerotised with massive pear-shaped scapus. The scapus was found broken in many females. Lateral lamellae formed frilled hem of the median plate. Copulatory openings near base of scapus (
